<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-02-04T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-02-04T20:00:00-05:00" n="839" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d839">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.5123/35: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-02-04T20:00:00-05:00">February 4, 1937—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>28. Your 53, February 2, 2 p.m., and 56, February 3, 2 p.m., in regard to
                            income tax. The Department approves your circularizing American consular
                            offices in China in the sense indicated in paragraphs 4 and 6 of
                            telegram No. 53.</p>
                        <p>The Department also approves the attitude and procedure outlined in the
                            last sentence of telegram 56.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>